 Despatch - Detectives from the Operational Command Centre in Uitenhage and detectives from SAPS Despatch are following up on all possible leads, after a 32-year-old male was wounded during a business robbery on Monday night. According to police informtion, the incidnet happened at about 18:30 at a business along Chief Albert Luthuli Street, in Khayamnandi, Despatch.            "It is alleged that the complainant and his assistant was standing outside their shop when they were approached by three men," described police spokesperson, Captain Gerda Swart. "The complainant sensed that something was not right and as he was about to run away, one of the three men pulled out a firearm and shot the complainant in the upperbody. "The suspects then forced the assistant back inside the shop and the suspects took cash and groceries." She added that the suspects then ran away from the scene on foot. "The 32-year-old male was rushed to a local hospital for medical treatment." Capt Swart said that Despatch police are investigating a case of business robbery and attempted murder. "No arrests were made as yet and the South African Police Service request," she said. "Anyone who might be able to assist with any information about the shooting incident or the business robbery , to contact Detective WO Wouter Verwey on 084 846 2273 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111." Callers may remain anonymous and all information will be treated with the strictest confidentiality. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 